  "text": "We have introduced a sensor based on gold electrode modified with 5,17-bis[N-(4-carboxypiperidino)metyhyl]-25,27,-bis(3-mercaptopropoxy)26,28-dihydroxycalix [CITATION_1] arene, dedicated to determining DA in the presence of the physiological concentration of AA and UA, as well as EP and NEP. The sensor discussed demonstrated a very good linear dynamic range, from 2.0 to10.0 pM, and a detection limit of 1.4 pM. One of its main advantages is the possibility to determine DA in the presence of other neurotransmitters, AA and UA. This is very important for future sensor applications in physiological samples control. The presented electrochemical sensor is very simple to prepare (which raises the possibility of effortless commercialization), easy to use, and could well be miniaturized. In this sensor, the analytical signal generation is based on the electroactivity of the calix [CITATION_2] arene-dopamine supramolecular complex. ",
